Privacy Policy for Pic Moments - Version 1

Effective date: 31/07/2023

Thank you for using Pic Moments app. This Privacy Policy is designed to help you understand how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal information while using the App. By using the App, you agree to the terms and conditions outlined in this Privacy Policy.

Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information:

The App may request and collect the following permissions from your device:
Camera Permission (android.permission.CAMERA): This permission is necessary to allow you to capture and upload photos and videos within the App.
Microphone Permission (android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO): This permission is required to enable you to record audio along with your photos and videos.
1.2 Non-Personal Information:

The App may collect non-personal information such as device information, usage patterns, and other technical data. This data is collected anonymously and is used to improve the App's performance, features, and user experience.
How We Use Your Information
2.1 Personal Information:

The personal information collected through the Camera and Microphone permissions will solely be used to provide you with the intended functionality of the App. We will not use or share your personal information for any other purposes without your explicit consent.
2.2 Non-Personal Information:

Non-personal information may be used for statistical analysis, to improve the App's performance and features, and to ensure the security and stability of the App.
Data Security
3.1 We prioritize the security of your personal information and have implemented appropriate technical and organizational measures to safeguard it against unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.

Third-Party Services
4.1 The App may utilize certain third-party services (e.g., cloud storage, analytics providers) to improve its functionality and services. These third-party services may have their own privacy policies, and we encourage you to review them as we are not responsible for their practices.

Children's Privacy
5.1 The App is not intended for use by children under the age of 15. We do not knowingly collect personal information from individuals under this age. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will promptly delete such information.

Changes to the Privacy Policy
6.1 We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices. When we make significant changes to this Policy, we will notify you through the App or other means as required by applicable law.

Contact Us
7.1 If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or the App's privacy practices, please contact us at kenalx1999@gmail.com.

By using the App, you agree to the terms and conditions outlined in this Privacy Policy.
